# Where files go

Follow **`docs/repository-layout-policy.md`** for full rules. Summary:

| Kind | Location |
|------|-----------|
| Library / runtime Python | `metacompressor/` only |
| Pytest (`test_*.py`) | `metacompressor/tests/` |
| Slow benchmarks, acceptance drivers | `benchmarks/` → reports under `results/` |
| Policies, ADRs, architecture prose | `docs/` (`docs/adr/` for ADRs) |
| CI/repo maintenance scripts | `scripts/` (not imported by `metacompressor`) |
| Cursor rules / skills / commands / subagents | `.cursor/rules`, `.cursor/skills`, `.cursor/commands`, `.cursor/agents` |
| Workspace editor defaults | `.vscode/` |
| Local scratch / CLI test dumps | `mc_test_output/`, `tmp_*` (gitignored) — never as sole spec |

Do not add production logic under `benchmarks/` or `results/`. Do not commit large generated blobs without team agreement; prefer regenerating from `benchmarks/`.

Before creating a file, pick the row above; if none fit, extend **`docs/repository-layout-policy.md`** in the same PR.
